CommonFields.Publication: Composites Part A: Applied Science and Manufacturing
CommonFields.Title: Dynamic mechanical analysis of fumed silica/cyanate ester nanocomposites
Author: Goertzen, William K.
Kessler, M.R.
CommonFields.Location: Department of Materials Science and Engineering, Iowa State University, Ames, IA 50011, USA

Matrix.Description: The matrix used was a low viscosity bisphenol E cyanate ester resin

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Before mixing the fumed silica was dried under vacuum

Filler.Description: The filler used was a hydrophilic fumed silica

Mixing.Description: The monomer was mixed with a 25 mm diameter high-shear blade. The silica was also added to the suspension while mixing. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

The suspension was sonicated with a 3.2 mm diameter probe tip at a frequency of 23 kHz. The power output ranged between 16 and 18 W. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C
the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C
additional sonication continued for 30 s. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

Additive.Description: A predetermined amount of catalyst was added to the dispersed suspension. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C
Additive.Additive: liquid phase organometallic-based polymerization catalyst (Bryte Technologies, EX-1510-B)

Mixing.Description: the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C
the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

MoldingInfo.Description: The suspensions were poured into high-temperature silicone rubber molds. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

Drying-Evaporation.Description: the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

Heating.Description: Suspensions were placed in a convection oven and cured. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C
During the curing process the oven was heated at a rate of 1 C/min to 180 C and held for 2 hours. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C
Curing process continued. Heated to 250 C at 1 C/min and held for 2 hrs. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

Cooling.Description: For the final step in curing, the suspensions were cooled to ambient temp. at 5 C/min. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

ChooseParameter.Other: Free-standing post-cures were conducted at temperatures of 180, 210, 240, and 270 C for 2 h. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Prior to testing all samples were dried and kept in a dry environment. the temperature of the suspension was maintained between 50 C and 65 C

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Equipment: TA Instruments (New Castle, Delaware, USA) dynamic mechanical analyzer (DMA) Q800
